                  </hi>. I was present at Stepney church when the prisoner was married to Mary Ann Warr—I cannot speak to the month—it may be twenty-one or twenty-two years ago—she lived with him after that—I saw her at Worship-street office when the prisoner was there—they were married at Stepney church.</p>
